item.content:
Formatting of this note might be different from the original.
You were seen in the ER for headache and back pain. You were given toradol and lidocaine patches in the ER.
If your pain worsens and you can't tolerate it at home, you develop new numbness/tingling, new weakness, inability to control your bladder or bowel or develop other new concerning symptoms return to the ER.
Follow up with neurology at your scheduled appointment.
Electronically signed by Alysia M. Horcher at 10/21/2019 6:25 PM CDT
